The paper presents a method for computing stable models of normal logic programs, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The method involves the use of coinduction, constructive negation, and other techniques, which are also relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the support for complex data structures, which suggests a possible connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
